From a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mega Promoting SRL <dev@megapromoting.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 09:00:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 0001] add /source disclosure endpoint (AGPL §13)

The GNU Affero GPL v3 §13 requires us to offer corresponding source code to
every user who interacts with the server over a network. We satisfy this by
serving a tiny HTTP route at `/_synapse/mdchat/source` that 302-redirects to
the public fork repository URL.

The repo URL is read from the MD_CHAT_SOURCE_URL environment variable so the
same patched image can serve mirrors or staging environments without rebuild.

Why a Python patch and not nginx-only:
  Nginx already serves `https://md-chat.eu/source`, but that hostname is a
  reverse-proxy convenience. AGPL §13 obligates the *Synapse process* itself
  to disclose source because federation peers and bots talk to Synapse on
  port 8448 without going through nginx. This route closes that gap.

